@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Product Roadmap";
}

<h1 class="display-4 mb-4">🛣️ Product Roadmap</h1>
<p class="lead">What's coming next. We're committed to making this the best session management system on the market.</p>

<hr class="my-4" />

<h2 class="mt-5">Recently shipped</h2>
<p class="text-muted">Live now on the web app at <a href="https://play.epegboard.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">play.epegboard.com</a>.</p>

<ul class="fs-5">
    <li>✅ <strong>Web app</strong> - runs in any browser on any device, no install</li>
    <li>✅ <strong>Algorithm improvements</strong> - significant ongoing work on the picker; addressing the most common complaint we heard (higher-rated players paired with weak partners)</li>
    <li>✅ <strong>Pick explanations</strong> - players can see exactly why each game was picked</li>
    <li>✅ <strong>Fairness statistics</strong> - visible mid-session</li>
    <li>✅ <strong>Ratings graphs</strong> - per-player rating progression over time</li>
    <li>✅ <strong>Attendance reports</strong> - built-in, helpful for member retention</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-5" />

<h2>Coming next</h2>
<p class="text-muted">Roughly in priority order. Dates aren't fixed - we ship features as they're ready, and the priority of each item reflects what we've heard from clubs in the field.</p>

<h3 class="mt-4">🎯 1. Picker enhancements</h3>
<p>The picker is our number-one priority and we're continuing to invest there:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>"Sticky" partner preferences</strong> - persistent pairing preferences (e.g. league partners) that the picker respects across a session</li>
    <li><strong>Single-discipline sessions</strong> - mixed-only or straight-only sessions, with the picker constraining game selection accordingly</li>
    <li><strong>Singles support</strong> - run singles-format sessions, not just doubles</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="mt-4">📊 2. More reporting</h3>
<p>Building on attendance reports, more visibility into how a club is running:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Head-to-head reports (member vs member win/loss + score history)</li>
    <li>Partnership reports (member-with-member win rate, frequency)</li>
    <li>Organiser insights - attendance fluctuations, court utilisation, payment status, picker-fairness trends</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="mt-4">🏆 3. Tournament support</h3>
<p>Run internal tournaments at your own club, plus inter-club tournaments between clubs using ePegboard.</p>

<h3 class="mt-4">📱 4. Phone display polish</h3>
<p>The web app works on phones today, but tablet or laptop-sized screens are the best experience. We're improving the phone display so smaller-screen use feels just as good.</p>

<hr class="my-5" />

<p class="text-muted">
    <em>Features and priorities may evolve based on user feedback and technical constraints. If something on this list matters to your club specifically, drop us a line at <a href="mailto:support@epegboard.com">support@epegboard.com</a> - it helps us prioritise.</em>
</p>

<p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
    <em>Note for desktop app users: most new functionality is being added to the web app at play.epegboard.com. The desktop app continues to be supported. Web-app sign-up is free at <a href="https://play.epegboard.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">play.epegboard.com</a> if you want to give it a try.</em>
</p>
